05471nam a22009255i 9783035608908DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20172017sz     fo  d z      eng d  a2017027811  a(OCoLC)994302246  a97830356089087 a10.1515/97830356089082doi  a(DE-B1597)467076  a(OCoLC)992489682  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH00aHT178.C552bZ46 2017 4aHT178.C552bZ46 2017 7aARC0100002bisacsh04a307.3/41609511322231 aZhou, Ying, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aUrban Loopholes :bCreative Alliances of Spatial Production in Shanghai’s City Center /cYing Zhou. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource (448 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tUrban Transformation in Diverse Inner-city Neighborhoods in Shanghai -- tChapter 1: Introduction -- tChapter 2: The Residential Neighborhood -- tChapter 3: The Cultural Street -- tChapter 4: The Midtown of China -- tChapter 5: The New Economies -- tChapter 6: The Contemporary Art Ecologies -- tChapter 7: Outlook -- tAcknowledgments -- tAbout the Author -- tIllustration Credits -- tIndex of Persons, Institutions, and Firms0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aEin strategisches Bündnis von städtischer Umnutzung, Kreativwirtschaft, Konsumökonomie und Denkmalschutz hat eine bemerkenswerte Transformation innerstädtischer Quartiere in Shanghai geschaffen. In einer Verbindung von intimen Kenntnissen der lokalen Szene und kritischer Distanz entwirft die Autorin ein genaues Bild der Strategien, Akteure und Prozesse eines spezifisch chinesischen Modells städtischer Transformation. Konzepte wie "urbane Fluchten", „Erhalten durch Bewohnen" und „Gentrifizierung in Chinesischer Manier" werden als charakteristisch für die Mechanismen dieser Stadtentwicklung Vorgestellt. Urban Loopholes führt die Unverzichtbarkeit der Resilienz urbaner Räume gegenüber dem Veränderungsdruck der Globalisierung vor Augen.  aUrban reuse, creative production, consumerism, and heritage protection have formed an alliance for the transformation of inner-city districts of Shanghai. This in-depth study, based on the author’s intimate familiarity of the local scene and supplemented by her critical outsider’s insights, describes the strategies, players, and processes of a uniquely Chinese model of urban transformation. Concepts like "Urban Loopholes", "Preservation via inhabitation", and "Gentrification with Chinese characteristics" characterize the specific mechanisms for urban development in Shanghai. Urban Loopholes invites the reader to rethink the necessity of urban resilience in the face of globalization’s impact for change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCity planningxChinaxShanghai. 0aCity planningzChinazShanghai. 0aSpace (Architecture)xChinaxShanghaixChinaxShanghai. 0aSpace (Architecture)zChinazShanghai. 0aUrban renewalxChinaxShanghai. 0aUrban renewalzChinazShanghai. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh1 aChristiaanse, Kees, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aChristiaanse, Kees, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2017z9783110547719oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z97831106252640 cEPUBz97830356088540 cprintz978303561104540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303560890840uhttps://www